			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Heheh, DAoC is Dark Age of Camelot, and unless you've been living under a rock, it's another online MMORPG.  The gripes mentioned below by Setsua and others is that EQ is getting rid of the things that make EQ, well, difficult.  My boss plays DAoC, and he was complaining that it took a whole day to get his NEW, untwinked cleric to level 30.  Seasoned players are justifiably concerned that Verant is trying to make EQ easier so that they can hold on to new players that think that EQ is just too hard.  I tend to agree.  While it's nice to be able to get my alts up easier, we wonder why we busted our asses to do what others can do with relative ease.<BR>
<BR>
I like some of the changes.  If they change coin weight and the ability to regain xp be praying over your corpse however, I'm out of here.  After playing my cleric for so long, and then having them adding rez abilities to level 14 as opposed to my 29, that bothered me.  I remember the sense of accomplishment I had at level 29 being able to bring back the dead.  And now paladins get rez at 22?  Why the hell did I make a cleric?  May as well give me dual wield, DoTs, and SoW.  Pretty soon VI is going make us all one giant class, with slightly better abilities.<BR>
<BR>
My rant.  My words.  Your time.  My apologies.
