	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It is good to vent (therapeutic) when something annoys you.  It also serves the purpose of seeing if anyone else has the problem.<BR>
<BR>
While looking over the posted patch I did not see (I could have missed it) verbage about the smoothing of the XP for lvl advancement nor meditating without the book, however I DID see mention of these when I patched last night.  I seemed to get mana at the same rate sitting as with the book.  However I find it interesting that someone has reported the meditate skill does not advance while sitting.  We should look out for it and report it as a bug if that is indeed the case.<BR>
<BR>
Regarding those that are up and throwing in the towel over a patch, take a breather, its just a game.  Do you toss your car just because it took 6 hours to fix your brakes instead of the 2 they told you it would take?  (you may take it to another shop next time but there is always DAoC...)<BR>
<BR>
Patching is frustrating, being locked out of the game is frustrating, but they probably have a 99+% uptime with most drops being a problem with the local ISP.<BR>
<BR>
That is not to say I don't have my own rant.  For the first time last night I was disconnected and the system would not let me back in saying I had an active player on the server.  Despite waiting 20 minutes and completely logging out, dropping my connection, reconnecting with a different ISP (even though it does not make a difference), and logging back in.  I just gave up and did something else.  So much for their patch addressing this problem, it was supposed to make sure you could log back in after 5 min no matter what.<BR>
<BR>
While it would be a bad thing if EQ and DAoC started to merge their features it is a GOOD thing to incorporate some of the better ideas or just plain making it more fun to play by removing some of the little annoyances without changing the balance or flavor of things.  <BR>
<BR>
What is so bad about Wizard criticals anyway???<BR>
<BR>
Seeryin, Ranger on Drinal
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
